Uses of Interface
xxl.core.collections.queues.Queue

  • Packages that use Queue 
    Package Description
    xxl.core.binarySearchTrees
    This package provides binary search trees by providing a generic binary search tree implementation that is used to implement avl-trees, bb-trees and red-black-trees.
    xxl.core.collections.queues
    The package xxl.core.collections.queues provides miscellaneous implementations of the queue datastructure.
    xxl.core.collections.queues.io
    The package xxl.core.collections.queues.io provides some implementations of the queue datastructure using special containers (BlockBasedQueue), files (FileStackQueue) or streams (StreamQueue) for storing and receiving the data.
    xxl.core.cursors.distincts
    The package xxl.core.cursors.distincts provides miscellaneous implementations of the distinct operator on cursors.
    xxl.core.cursors.groupers
    The package xxl.core.cursors.groupers provides miscellaneous implementations of the group operator on cursors.
    xxl.core.cursors.identities
    The package xxl.core.cursors.identities provides miscellaneous implementations of identity operators on cursors.
    xxl.core.cursors.sorters
    The package xxl.core.cursors.sorters provides miscellaneous implementations of sort operators on cursors.
    xxl.core.cursors.sources.io
    The package xxl.core.cursors.sources.io provides miscellaneous implementations of source operators that use I/O operations to retrieve their data.
    xxl.core.cursors.unions
    The package xxl.core.cursors.unions provides miscellaneous implementations of the union operator on cursors.
    xxl.core.cursors.wrappers
    The package xxl.core.cursors.wrappers provides miscellaneous implementations of wrapper classes that make an object representing an arbitrary form of iteration via the cursor interface.
    xxl.core.indexStructures
    Provides important index structures like B-trees, R-trees, M-trees and bulk-loading-algorithms.
    xxl.core.indexStructures.rtrees  
    xxl.core.relational.cursors
    The package provides a whole algebra of cursors that extends the functionality of the classes cursors.
    xxl.core.spatial.cursors
    Provides mappers for different type of Point and Rectangle objects as well as several join algorithms: nested loops distance similarity-join for Points, the spatial join algorithm based on space-filling curves proposed by Jack Orenstein, similarity-join algorithm "GESS: Generic External Space Sweep" and hash-based plane sweep for two-dimensional data.

      Subinterfaces of Queue in xxl.core.collections.queues 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  FIFOQueue<E>
      The interface FIFO queue represents a FIFO (first in, first out) iteration over a collection of elements (also known as a sequence) with a peek method.
      interface  LIFOQueue<E>
      The interface LIFO queue represents a LIFO (last in, first out) iteration over a collection of elements (also known as a sequence) with a peek method.
      interface  MemoryManageableQueue<E> 
      Classes in xxl.core.collections.queues that implement Queue 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AbstractMemoryManageableQueue<E> 
      class  AbstractQueue<E>
      This class provides a skeletal implementation of the Queue interface, to minimize the effort required to implement this interface.
      class  ArrayQueue<E>
      This class provides a resizable-array implementation of the Queue interface with a FIFO (first in, first out) strategy.
      class  BoundedQueue<E>
      Decorates an arbitrary queue by adding boundary conditions.
      class  DecoratorQueue<E>
      This class provides a decorator for a queue that follows the Decorator Design Pattern (for further details see Structural Patterns, Decorator in Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software by Erich Gamma, Richard Helm, Ralph Johnson, and John Vlissides).
      class  DistinctQueue<E>
      This class provides a wrapper for a queue that performes a simple duplicate elimination.
      class  DynamicHeap<E>
      This class provides a dynamical resizable-array implementation of the heap datastructure.
      class  Heap<E>
      This class provides the heap datastructure.
      class  ListQueue<E>
      This class provides an implementation of the Queue interface with a FIFO (first in, first out) strategy that internally uses a list to store its elements.
      class  MemoryManageableListQueue<E> 
      class  StackQueue<E>
      This class provides an implementation of the Queue interface with a LIFO (last in, first out) strategy that internally uses a stack to store its elements.
      class  ThreadsafeQueue<E>
      A ThreadsafeQueue can be used by different threads that use this queue for communicating with each other.
      class  UnmodifiableQueue<E>
      This class provides a decorator for a given queue that cannot be modified.
